remium economyedit on december   american announced a new premium economy product for most longhaul widebody aircraft this new product will debut on the new s in late  and will be available on the new as in  it will also be retrofitted to all other widebody aircraft within the next three years excluding s due to their upcoming retirement the seats will be wider than standard main cabin seats and will offer  of pitch  more than main cabin extra seats as well as a footrest premium economy customers will also get two free checked bags priority boarding and enhanced food and drink service including free alcohol this product will make american airlines the first us carrier to offer a fourcabin aircraft main cabin extraedit americans economy plus product not to be confused with premium economy main cabin extra is available on most of the mainline fleet and american eagle regional aircraft with more than  seats exceptions include a majority of former us airways aircraft as of may  us airways express regional aircraft and a handful of ers that have yet to be retrofitted seats range from – inches – cm in width and have – inches – cm of pitch which is – more inches of pitch offered in regular economy seating american will retain main cabin extra when the new premium economy product enters service in late  main cabinedit main cabin is americans economy product and is found on all mainline and regional aircraft in its fleet seats range from – inches – cm in width and have – inches – cm of pitch newer aircraft including all boeing er refurbished boeing ers all boeing  dreamliners all airbus as all newly delivered airbus as and boeing s and most newly delivered airbus as include seatback tvs featuring avod in each seatcitation needed basic economyedit americans basic economy product basic economy is available on select routes it is americans lowest main cabin fare basic economy is located in main cabin but comes with restrictions these restrictions include assigned seat at check in no access to overhead bins no upgrades or refunds and boarding in the last group american airlines marketed increased legroom in economy class as more room throughout coach also referred to as mrtc starting in february  two rows of economy class seats were removed on boeing  and mcdonnell douglas md aircraft amid financial losses this scheme was discontinued in  in may  american announced they would be adding more seats to some of its boeing  max jetliners and reducing overall legroom in the basic economy class the last three rows will lose two inches going from the current  to  inches the remainder of the economy cabin will have  inches of legroom this compares to jet blue with  inches of legroom and spirit with  inches aadvantageedit main article aadvantage this section needs expansion with a decent summary of the contents of the main article see wikipediasummary style you can help by adding to it april  aadvantage logo present aadvantage is the frequent flyer program for american airlines it was launched on may   and it remains the largest frequent flyer program with over  million members as of  loungesedit this section needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed december  learn how and when to remove this template message admirals clubedit admirals club logo inside an admirals club the admirals club was conceived by aa president cr smith as a marketing promotion shortly after he was made an honorary texas ranger inspired by the kentucky colonels and other honorary organizations smith decided to make particularly valued passengers admirals of the flagship fleet aa called its aircraft flagships at the time the list of admirals included many celebrities politicians and other vips as well as more ordinary customers who had been particularly loyal to the airline there was no physical admirals club until shortly after the opening of laguardia airport during the airports construction new york mayor fiorello laguardia had an upperlevel lounge set aside for press conferences and business meetings at one such press conference he noted that the entire terminal was being offered for lease to airline tenants after a reporter asked whether the lounge would be leased as well laguardia replied that it would and a vice president of aa immediately offered to lease the premises the airline then procured a liquor license and began operating the lounge as the admirals club in citation needed the second admirals club opened at washington national airport because it was illegal to sell alcohol in virginia at the time the club contained refrigerators for the use of its members so they could store their own liquor at the airportcitation needed for many years membership in the admirals club and most other airline lounges was by the airlines invitation after a passenger sued for discrimination the club and most other airline lounges switched to a paid membership program flagship loungeedit though affiliated with the admirals club and staffed by many of the same employees the flagship lounge is a separate lounge specifically designed for customers flying in first class on transcontinental domestic flights and international flights as well as aadvantage executive platinum and oneworld emerald frequent flyers flagship lounges are now available at four airports chicagoohare londonheathrow los angeles and new yorkjfk american also previously offered a flagship lounge in miami from  to  and again from  it plans to open again in  accidents and incidentsedit main article american airlines accidents and incidents this section needs expansion with a decent summary of the contents of the main article see wikipediasummary style you can help by adding to it april  in popular cultureedit in the s mattel released a series of american airlines stewardess barbie dolls throughout the s american airlines was featured in john hughes home alone trilogy of movies in august  in a season  episode of mad men episode  titled flight  pete campbells father is a passenger on american airlines flight  which crashes shortly after takeoff from idlewild airport now john f kennedy international airport killing all the passengers and crew on board american airlines was a sponsor of a travelogue segment of the univision show sábado gigante titled la cámara viajera american airlines was extensively featured in the  movie up in the air as part of a marketing tiein between the airline and paramount pictures in  american airlines collaborated with disney to promote planes by featuring a cameo appearance of a passenger airliner named tripp with the new american airlines livery to promote its new image airport  used a boeing  freighter cargo variant sn  registration n leased from american airlines see alsoedit dallasfort worth portal companies portal aviation portal aairpass air transportation in the united states list of airlines of the united states list of airports in the united states referencesedit  a b american airlines chaviation retrieved december     f with change  and change  and change  pdf federal aviation administration october   p  retrieved december     a b history of american airlines american airlines inc  retrieved june     airline certificate information – detail view avinfofaagov federal aviation administration may   certificate number aalaa   a b oneworld at a glance oneworld november  retrieved december     american airlines group − about us − american airlines aacom retrieved    associated the september   american air signs deal to contract out some flying to skywest yahoo news retrieved october     koenig david november   american airlines parent seeks ch  protection google news associated press archived from the original on december   retrieved  december    httpswwwbritannicacomtopicamericanairlines  corporate structure american airlines retrieved  may   american airlines group overview archived copy at 