northern california hub either in san jose or san francisco the san jose hub was inherited with the acquisition of reno air reno air had made san jose a hub in the mids after american had decided that the competition on the west coast made the hub unprofitable and closed it maintenance basesedit dallasfort worth international airport  primary base for airbus a and a aircraft boeing  and  aircraft secondary base for boeing    and mcdonnell douglas md aircraft laguardia airport  american operates a small maintenance base for boeing  and erj aircraft pittsburgh international airport  primary base for all legacy us airways airbus aircraft tulsa international airport  primary base for all of americans boeing fleet with the exception of the  and  as well as american eagle aircraft destinationsedit main article american airlines destinations this section needs expansion with a decent summary of the contents of the main article see wikipediasummary style you can help by adding to it april  aa aircraft at concourse d of miami international airport in april  aa boeing  at augusto c sandino international airport managua in january  aa boeing  at galeão international airport rio de janeiro in november  american operated interchange flight services in conjunction with alaska airlines during the s between texas and alaska during the construction of the transalaska oil pipeline this interchange agreement allowed for single no change of aircraft service between houston texas and dallasfort worth texas and anchorage alaska and fairbanks alaska the round trip routing of this interchange flight was houstondallasfort worthseattleanchoragefairbanks with seattle washington serving as the interchange point where flight and cabin crews were changed from one airline to the other boeing  jetliners provided by both american and alaska airlines were utilized to provide this interchange servicecitation needed american airlines is the only us carrier that flies to barranquilla belo horizonte bra